**Skills I Learned from the Excel Analysis**
 working with this Excel analysis, I developed several useful skills related to data analysis and interpretation. First, I learned how to organize and structure raw data in Excel so it becomes easier to analyze and compare. This helped me understand how important clear data organization is  business analysis.
During the task, I worked with indicators such as **revenue share, profit contribution, average order value (AOV), and average order frequency (AOF)**. By analyzing these metrics, I learned how different customer groups contribute to the company’s overall performance.
Another important skill I improved was interpreting numerical results. I learned not only how to calculate values in Excel but also how to explain what these numbers mean  the business. This helped me better understand customer behavior and purchasing patterns.
Overall, this task improved my confidence in using Excel  analytical work, strengthened my ability to work with business data, and helped me present analytical insights in a clear and simple way.
